postcontent:
FOR SALE:
Molot VEPR 7.62x54R (20.5" barrel, integrated sights, slant receiver, 2 5-round magazines) and a POSP 8x42 D scope (1000m illuminated reticle, fine focus diopter ring).

I bought this rifle from Centerfire Systems in the spring of 2013. They offered up a few of these at a sale price of $750 for one day while they were normally selling them at around $1000. I had been keeping my eye on the price and jumped on the deal when I saw it. Since I've purchased it I've put about 220 round through it (split a 440 round can with a friend).

PRICE:
Right now these are being sold (with square receiver) for $729. The POSP 8x42 D costs $280.

So, $729 for the VEPR + $20 FFL fee + $20 shipping + $280 for the scope + $15 shipping = $1064

I'M OFFERING THE RIFLE AND SCOPE FOR $700, FIRM.

If you're not picking this up locally, then it will cost $20 to have it shipped from my FFL to yours. If you're local and would like to inspect this in person, I can meet up with you at a range and I'll let you look it over, shoot it, etc..

WHY I'M SELLING:
Have you heard about the upcoming changes to the NFA regulations? Well, they are going to start requiring fingerprints, photos and law enforcement signatures even if you are getting your NFA items through a trust, LLC, corporation, etc.. This really sucks for people like me who live in a county where CLEOs refuse to sign off on the paperwork. Basically if I want to own any NFA stuff, I have a small window here to set up a trust, purchase some NFA items, pay the tax stamps, and submit my paperwork to the ATF, before the changes come into effect. (The other option would be to move to a different county, but I can't do that right now.) That's what I'm putting the funds from this rifle towards.

Thanks for looking.

The rifle has been sold!
